Data:
As input, the script accepts from the user the date of the problem in YYYY-MM-DD format.
The output is an archive of log files in .zip format with files from the date the problem occurred and the day before.

Attached files:
collectlog.sh - script for collecting logs
files.txt - a list of directories/files to collect, as well as a list of exclusions.

Script run command:
sudo /bin/bash collectlog.sh files.txt
